<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870818-0087 </DOCNO><HL> K mart Earnings Rose23% in Second Period</HL><DD> 08/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> KMEARNINGS (ERN)RETAILING (RET) </IN><DATELINE> TROY, Mich.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   K mart Corp. posted a 23% increase in second-quarter net income on a sales gain of 7.2%.    The company earned $145.4 million, or 71 cents a share, compared with year-earlier net of $118.4 million, or 59 cents a share. Year-earlier results included a $200,000 loss fron discontinued operations. Sales rose to $6.3 billion from $5.88 billion.    The retailer attributed the improvement in sales and earnings to its merchandising and advertising.    K mart shares closed yesterday at $44.875, down $1.125, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading.    In the first half, K mart profit rose 24% to $260.9 million, or $1.28 a share, from $210 million, or $1.06 a share, a year earlier. In the first half of 1986, the retailer recorded a $500,000 loss from discontinued operations. Sales increased 8.2% to $11.9 billion from $11 billion.    K mart's chairman, Bernard M. Fauber, said in a statement that he remains optimistic about the second-half outlook, but he didn't issue any specific predictions. &quot;Consumers are responding well to K mart's back-to-school merchandising programs, including fall apparel and traditional school supplies,&quot; he said. </TEXT></DOC>